A Brief History
Founded in 1945, the Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove has a storied past marked by milestones and achievements. Originally established as a branch of Charles University in Prague, it quickly garnered recognition for its commitment to academic excellence and groundbreaking research initiatives. Over the decades, it has evolved into a leading institution, attracting students and faculty from around the globe.

